msgid "Idha no, āvuso, ko viseso, ko adhippayāso, kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ samaṇassa vā gotamassa amhākaṃ vā, yadidaṃ, dhammadesanāya vā dhammadesanaṃ, anusāsaniyā vā anusāsaninti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn46.54:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandimha nappaṭikkosimha, anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamimha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn46.54:10.2"
msgid "‘bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn46.54:11.1"
msgid "“Evaṃvādino, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say to them: "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ bhāvitā panāvuso, mettācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "‘But reverends, how is the heart’s release by love developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā panāvuso, karuṇācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "How is the heart’s release by compassion developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā panāvuso, muditācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "How is the heart’s release by rejoicing developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.5"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā panāvuso, upekkhācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā’ti? "
msgstr "How is the heart’s release by equanimity developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end?’ "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.6"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhā, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā na ceva sampāyissanti, uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjissanti. "
msgstr "Questioned like this, the wanderers who follow other paths would be stumped, and, in addition, would get frustrated. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.8"
msgid "Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmiṃ. "
msgstr "Because they’re out of their element. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:11.9"
msgid "Nāhaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo imesaṃ pañhānaṃ veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyya, aññatra tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā ito vā pana sutvā. "
msgstr "I don’t see anyone in this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—who could provide a satisfying answer to these questions except for the Realized One or his disciple or someone who has heard it from them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.119, sc12
msgctxt "sn46.54:12.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, mettācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "And how is the heart’s release by love developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mettāsahagataṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe … mettāsahagataṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the heart’s release by love together with the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.3"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.4"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.5"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.6"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.7"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūlañca paṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako ca tattha viharati sato sampajāno, subhaṃ vā kho pana vimokkhaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:12.8"
msgid "Subhaparamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, mettācetovimuttiṃ vadāmi, idhapaññassa bhikkhuno uttarivimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato. "
msgstr "The apex of the heart’s release by love is the beautiful, I say, for a mendicant who has not penetrated to a higher freedom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.120, sc13
msgctxt "sn46.54:13.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, karuṇācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "And how is the heart’s release by compassion developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:13.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu karuṇāsahagataṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe … karuṇāsahagataṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the heart’s release by compassion together with the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:13.3"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati … pe … "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. … "

msgctxt "sn46.54:13.4"
msgid "sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūlañca paṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:13.5"
msgid "Sabbaso vā pana rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Or else, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:13.6"
msgid "Ākāsānañcāyatanaparamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, karuṇācetovimuttiṃ vadāmi, idhapaññassa bhikkhuno uttarivimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato. "
msgstr "The apex of the heart’s release by compassion is the dimension of infinite space, I say, for a mendicant who has not penetrated to a higher freedom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn46.54:14.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, muditācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "And how is the heart’s release by rejoicing developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:14.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu muditāsahagataṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe … muditāsahagataṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the heart’s release by rejoicing together with the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:14.3"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati … pe … "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. … "

msgctxt "sn46.54:14.4"
msgid "sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūlañca paṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:14.5"
msgid "Sabbaso vā pana ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Or else, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:14.6"
msgid "Viññāṇañcāyatanaparamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, muditācetovimuttiṃ vadāmi, idhapaññassa bhikkhuno uttarivimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato. "
msgstr "The apex of the heart’s release by rejoicing is the dimension of infinite consciousness, I say, for a mendicant who has not penetrated to a higher freedom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.121, sc15
msgctxt "sn46.54:15.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, upekkhācetovimutti, kiṅgatikā hoti, kiṃparamā, kiṃphalā, kiṃpariyosānā? "
msgstr "And how is the heart’s release by equanimity developed? What is its destination, apex, fruit, and end? "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upekkhāsahagataṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … upekkhāsahagataṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the heart’s release by equanimity together with the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.3"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.4"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.5"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.6"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.7"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati ‘appaṭikūlañca paṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.8"
msgid "Sabbaso vā pana viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Or else, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "sn46.54:15.9"
msgid "Ākiñcaññāyatanaparamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, upekkhācetovimuttiṃ vadāmi, idhapaññassa bhikkhuno uttarivimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato”ti. "
msgstr "The apex of the heart’s release by equanimity is the dimension of nothingness, I say, for a mendicant who has not penetrated to a higher freedom.” "

